    "Additionally, the variance is a truncated variable, which can lead to further heteroskedasticity in the regression residuals.",
    "To combat the influence of these two effects, we implemented a conservative clipping of data with exceptionally high variance, and a correction for heteroskedasticity in the form of iterative regression with residual weighting.",
    "The result of these processes (compared to simple linear regression) is presented in panels b and c of Fig. 28.Once the value of α S is computed per bin, the original measurement variances (for sources in that bin) are corrected by subtracting the inferred leakage amplitude per source i:ν ′ ε,i = ν ε,i -α S S ε,i.",
    "(22)A170, page 29 of 54 The distribution of α S values measured after this correction (i.e. re-fitting Eq.",
    "(21) with ν ε,i → ν ′ ε,i) are shown in panel d of Fig. 28."
